	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>7th Sep 23 Elul 5623</date></p>
				<p>The <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Many thanks for the<lb/> photographs you so kindly sent me<lb/> in your favor of <date>1st</date>.  One copy<lb/> <persName>Mrs De Sola</persName> will give to <persName>Mrs J A Joseph</persName><lb/> as you promised her one&#8212;the other<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> which means that both my wife<lb/> and myself will be proud to preserve<lb/> in our album the lineaments of<lb/> one we so highly esteem&#44; and who<lb/> deserves so well of <placeName>Israel</placeName>.  I wish<lb/> with the <persName>Payton</persName> I could add the<lb/> scriptural <add>Hebrew</add>&#8212;but I cannot<lb/> have the pleasure of <hi rend="underline">exchanging</hi></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>for the simple reason that<lb/> I do not possess a photographic<lb/> portrait of either myself or my<lb/> better half&#8212;besides&#44; I am afraid<lb/> you would find my exchange if<lb/> not looking exactly like <persName>Isaac&#39;s</persName><lb/> of old&#44; yet having something<lb/> <hi rend="underline">sheepish</hi> about it.  As soon as<lb/> I have copies I will send them.<lb/>  I have just had the inexpressible<lb/> pleasure of receiving home a<lb/> capital likeness&#8212;more beautifully<lb/> &#38; successfully done&#8212;of my late<lb/> father <add>Hebrew</add>.  It was taken from<lb/> a photograph done some 17 years<lb/> ago&#44; and is a faithful representation<lb/> of what he was at that period.<lb/>  The copy just done for me is<lb/> also by a Jewish artist&#44; a member<lb/> of my congregation&#44; and is life size.</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>This leads me to tell you that I<lb/> have completed the Biography and<lb/> sent the M.S. to the family.  After<lb/> the Holy days I shall see about its<lb/> publication.  <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You have said it.  My<lb/> own work deprives me the pleasure<lb/> of corresponding with many esteemed<lb/> friends.  I may add without flattery<lb/> that with no one sooner than<lb/> yourself would I desire frequently&#44;<lb/> to exchange thoughts&#44; as I think<lb/> we belong pretty much to the same<lb/> school.  But my ordinary avocations<lb/> and the education&#8212;or rather&#44;<lb/> superintendence of the education<lb/> of my children leave me little<lb/> leisure.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Sarah Joseph</persName> has just<lb/> come in and desires me to say<lb/> she would not accept the</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>duplicate photograph even if I<lb/> gave it her&#44; as she does not think<lb/> it good&#44; but wishes you to send<lb/> her another kind.  Another member<lb/> of my congregation <add>&#63;</add> artist who spent<lb/> <date>Friday</date> evening with us thinks it<lb/> a capital thing artistically speaking&#44;<lb/> Still I also like the one in which you<lb/> are represented sitting in a chair<lb/> and would like to obtain a copy if<lb/> procurable.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I shall speak to <persName>Wm<lb/> Benjamin</persName> about his father&#39;s indebtedness<lb/> and hope to write you again after<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add>.  Meanwhile receive my best<lb/> wishes &#40;and my wife&#39;s too&#41; for your<lb/> well&#45;being</p>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add><lb/> <add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Yours faithfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
				<p rend="The following is written sideways in the left margin.">Please hand enclosed to <persName>Miss Gratz</persName>.</p>
		</body>
